Eaga Gets 300 Million-Pound Funding for U.K. Solar Project

-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 
2011-03-17T13:40:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/eaga-gets-300-million-pounds-funding-for-u-k-solar-photovoltaic-project.html
  Eaga Plc (EAGA) , a U.K. energy-efficiency
provider, said it arranged 300 million pounds ($484 million) of
financing for a project to install solar photovoltaic panels on
the roofs of residential buildings.  The funding includes 225 million pounds of loans from HSBC
Holdings Plc, Lloyds Banking Group Plc, National Bank of
Australia Ltd., Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc and Banco
Santander SA, the Newcastle, England-based company said in a
statement.  Eaga will also use 75 million pounds of equity, of which 60
million pounds will come from infrastructure funds managed by
HSBC and  Barclays Capital , according to the statement. Eaga will
invest the remaining 15 million pounds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Eeuwens in  London  
 keeuwens@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 fkhan33@bloomberg.net . 